# 18. What Makes Candidates Fail

Usually not lack of intelligence.

Mostly:

* shallow understanding
* inability to explain clearly
* panic during follow-up questions
* no real projects
* weak SQL
* weak debugging skills

Interviewers care A LOT about:
“Can this person work on a real backend system?”

---

# 19. Final Goal

Your target should NOT be:
“I want to memorize Spring Boot.”

Your target should be:
“I want to think like a backend engineer.”

That means:

* understanding internals
* explaining tradeoffs
* caring about scalability
* writing maintainable code
* debugging confidently
* thinking about production systems

That is what gets people hired.
